# ABAC & condition keys

## Conditions make policies context-aware

High-leverage keys:

- **`aws:MultiFactorAuthPresent`** — force MFA (with `Deny`)
- **`aws:SourceIp`** — office / VPN ranges
- **`aws:RequestedRegion`** — region restriction
- **`aws:PrincipalOrgID`** — only your org's principals
- **`aws:SecureTransport`** — require HTTPS
- **`sts:ExternalId` / `aws:SourceArn`** — confused-deputy

## ABAC — tag-based access

Built on **`aws:PrincipalTag`** + **`aws:ResourceTag`**. Effect depends on **tags**, not hard-coded ARNs.

Tag principal `Project=Atlas`, tag resource `Project=Atlas` → **one** policy: allow when the tags **match**.

**New project → no new policies.** Just tag the identities and resources; access flows. The scaling pattern when permission sets would otherwise explode.
